The road authority has commissioned a comprehensive route survey of Roc Road, the principal transit corridor connecting Midgaard to the eastern districts. The current documentation is outdated and fails to account for changes to way stations, branching paths, and side approaches since the last formal survey. Traverse the full extent of the road and return with a complete route record. The data feeds into convoy planning, hazard tracking, and tariff assessment.
The Roc Road survey is complete and the route documentation has been filed with the road authority archive. The warden corps has already adjusted patrol planning based on the new route data, and convoy operators have begun using the updated manifest coverage for the current transit season.

